commit_message:
perf: Avoid stat call for ~/.ccache if CCACHE_DIR is set

Closes #1541.

issues.title: Reduce stat calls to $HOME/.ccache for configuration lookup
issues.body:
We have home directories on NFS and these are sometimes rather slow. When stracing the builds we found that ccache was checking for non existing $HOME/.ccache for each call even though we have configuration set using environment variable.

Looking at the code legacy_ccache_dir).is_directory() is always called quite early in "Config::read" and the result used much later if at all.
https://github.com/ccache/ccache/blob/852f0740dc746364b5c5bc604e01afd9f7e365d8/src/ccache/config.cpp#L596

Can I suggest moving the check inside the else if?
https://github.com/ccache/ccache/blob/852f0740dc746364b5c5bc604e01afd9f7e365d8/src/ccache/config.cpp#L635

Thank you
